# Figma API Configuration
# Follow these steps to set up your integration:

# STEP 1: Get your Personal Access Token
# 1. Open Figma and click on your profile/avatar (top left)
# 2. Go to "Settings"
# 3. Scroll down to "Personal access tokens"
# 4. Click "Generate new token", give it a name, and copy the token
FIGMA_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_figma_personal_access_token_here

# STEP 2: Get your Figma File ID
# 1. Open the Figma file you want to sync
# 2. Copy the file ID from the URL:
#    URL: https://www.figma.com/file/ABCD1234EFGH5678/Project-Name
#    File ID: ABCD1234EFGH5678 (the part between /file/ and the project name)
FIGMA_FILE_ID=q0S5vyoeadYuVidGbPDnTM

# Brand node IDs are configured in figma.config.js:
#   Energia:  39:343   (Colour Primitives, Energia)
#   Power NI: 43:1488  (Colour Primitives, Power NI)
#
# Sync tokens from Figma:
#   npm run figma:tokens:energia   → tokens/energia/
#   npm run figma:tokens:powerNI   → tokens/powerNI/
#   npm run figma:tokens           → activeBrand from figma.config.js
#
# Set which brand this project uses in figma.config.js (activeBrand)

# Token scopes needed: file_content:read, file_metadata:read, library_assets:read
# For Variables API (optional): file_variables:read

# https://www.figma.com/design/q0S5vyoeadYuVidGbPDnTM/Foundations-File?node-id=0-1&t=fRM8dqlioZpvH6p5-1